olive oil
1 parsnip
1 sachet dried oregano
½ pear
1 packet red pesto
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet chicken breast
½ tbs plain flour
1 drizzle red wine vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
2 Kumara
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Peel and cut kumara into bite-sized chunks. Cut parsnip into bite-sized chunks.
• Place kumara, parsnip and dried oregano on a lined oven tray. Drizzle generously with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Add a dash of water to the tray, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice pear (see ingredients).
• In a small bowl, combine red pesto and mayonnaise. Set aside.
• Place your hand flat on top of each chicken breast and use a sharp knife to slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a shallow bowl, combine plain flour and Nan's special seasoning, then season. Coat chicken in flour mixture, then transfer to a plate.

• When the veggies have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base of the pan.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken, in batches, until golden and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel.
• Meanwhile, combine a drizzle of red wine vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl, then season. Add pear and mixed salad leaves. Toss to coat.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Slice chicken.
• Divide chicken, oregano-roasted veggies and pear salad between plates.
• Sprinkle the grated Parmesan cheese over the chicken.
• Serve with red pesto mayo.